sudo bash Anaconda3-2019.10-Linux-x86_64.sh #regret. shouldn't have used sudo. caused many problems of write permission
press enter repeatedly to finish reading the document (before installation begins)
set /home/lenovo/Music/anaconda3 as the installation directory
after the installation finished) source ~/.bashrc (after it, there will be a (base) before your username in command line. no need to worry about it)
(then, in commmand line, you should be able to use the command conda)
